  🎨 CLIENT DEPLOYMENT (React to Vercel)

  1. Build the client:

  cd /Users/koded/Code/Fog-of-War/fog-of-war/client
  npm install
  npm run build

  2. Deploy to Vercel:

  Option A: Command line
  npm i -g vercel
  vercel login
  vercel deploy

  Option B: GitHub integration
  - Push code to GitHub
  - Go to vercel.com
  - Click "New Project"
  - Select your GitHub repo
  - Set build command: npm run build
  - Set output directory: dist
  - Click "Deploy"

  3. Set environment variable on Vercel:

  For production:
  VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://your-server-domain.com

  For development (local):
  VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8080

  Update .env file:
  VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://your-server-domain.com

  4. Redeploy after env changes:

  vercel deploy --prod

  ---
  📋 Deployment Checklist:

  Server:

  - Build Go binary
  - Set all .env variables (especially JWT_SECRET, SOLANA_HOUSE_PRIVATE_KEY)
  - Deploy to hosting (Railway, Render, VPS, Docker)
  - Note the server URL (e.g., https://fog-server.railway.app)
  - Enable TLS/SSL certificate
  - Test gRPC connection

  Client:

  - Run npm run build locally to test
  - Push to GitHub
  - Deploy to Vercel
  - Set VITE_BACKEND_URL environment variable pointing to your server
  - Test wallet connection and gameplay

  ---
  🔗 URL Format:

  Backend URL (for client .env):
  https://your-server-domain.com
  Example: https://fog-server.railway.app

  Vercel URL (for users):
  https://your-project.vercel.app
  Example: https://fog-of-war.vercel.app

